               <!--saint-->
               <floruit notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699"> 
                  He was a saint of the 17th century, contemporary of 
                  <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>Susǝnyos</persName>. 
                  At the age  of twelve, he went to the monastery of 
                  <placeName ref="LOC2352DabraS">Dabra Dabsān</placeName>
                  to take monastic orders and was ordained priest by the metropolitan ṗāṗṗās 
                 
                  <persName ref="PRS6071Krestodo"> 
                     <roleName type="title">ʾabuna</roleName>Krǝstodolu [II]</persName>.
                  As a follower of <persName ref="PRS3932Ewostate">ʾEwosṭātewos</persName>, 
                  he professed the Unionist doctrine during the Christological controversies. 
                  Because of his beliefs, <persName ref="PRS1280Abranyos">ʾAbrānyos</persName> 
                  was imprisoned by 
                  <persName ref="PRS9152TaklaHa">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>Takla Hāymānot I</persName> 
                  and released by 
                  <persName ref="PRS9449Tewoflos">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>Tewoflos</persName>. Thereafter, 
                  he returned to his monastery <placeName ref="LOC2390DabraT">Dabra Ṭǝllul</placeName>
                  where he remained until his death.
                  He was succeeded by <persName ref="PRS1578AkalaKr">ʾAkāla Krǝstos</persName>.
                  
                  
               </floruit>
           
               
